He tried to steal a Picasso
in Madrid five years ago,

00:12:38.693 --> 00:12:41.395
but a guard shot him in the left
shoulder, and he fled empty-handed.

00:12:41.529 --> 00:12:43.073
Okay, so why can't
anybody find this guy?

00:12:43.097 --> 00:12:44.265
Because he might not exist.

00:12:44.965 --> 00:12:46.601
- He could be a myth.
- What do you mean?

00:12:46.735 --> 00:12:48.302
I mean, it's impressive work,

00:12:48.435 --> 00:12:51.014
but the name Jean-Baptiste comes
up whenever there's a heist unsolved,

00:12:51.038 --> 00:12:54.341
the thief got in and out without a
trace, escaped with another masterpiece.

00:12:54.475 --> 00:12:55.776
Must be Jean-Baptiste.

00:12:55.909 --> 00:12:59.179
But is he real? Maybe.
It could be ten different guys.

00:12:59.313 --> 00:13:01.849
Check this out.
I searched public records.

00:13:01.982 --> 00:13:04.302
Someone sued claiming to be
the Rembrandt's rightful owner.

00:13:04.418 --> 00:13:06.053
We have a name?

00:13:06.186 --> 00:13:08.098
Yeah, an Ari Weisman, but it
looks like the records are sealed.

00:13:08.122 --> 00:13:10.525
Ari would be the first guy to
take matters into his own hands

00:13:10.659 --> 00:13:12.899
- when the court ruled against him.
- -We got an address?

00:13:13.027 --> 00:13:14.562
Yeah, looks like he's local.

00:13:15.095 --> 00:13:18.999
Captain, I could use a hand from
Detectives Ozdil and Forrester for a bit.

